text: Loïc Gasch (born 13 August 1994) is a Swiss high jumper. He finished tenth at the 2018 European Championships. He also competed at the 2015 European U23 Championships without reaching the final. His personal best jump is 2.26 metres, achieved in July 2017 in Zürich. ==References== Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:Swiss male high jumpers
